You have created a public key and private key for use with SSH. The contents of which keyshould be copied to a remote host in order to enable authentication?
A)  The public key.
B)  The private key.
C)  Both the public and private keys.
D)  Neither the public nor the private key. It must be generated on the remote host.
A
A. The public key should be copied to the remote host. When it is copied and the contentsplaced into ~/.ssh/authorized_keys, authentication will be allowed from anyonepresenting the corresponding private key.
